Scott has a Masters in Organization Development and over 10 years of experience in the field, specializing in facilitation, e-learning and online community development, marketing, and business strategy. He is a fluent Spanish speaker, certified ASTD trainer, was selected as part of the Masie Center’s 30 under 30 program at the Learning 2012 conference where he also lead a session about online community development, and has worked in Thailand, Laos, El Salvador, China, Kyrgyzstan, and Canada.
Over the last five years, Scott has focused on online learning and collaboration tool development in an international context - specifically with USAID, UNICEF, and the World Bank. When working on these projects, Scott emphasized the importance of engaging stakeholders in follow-up communications. He has been invited regularly to lecture at the University of Pennsylvania’s Chief Learning Officer PhD Program. In addition, Scott has led the design, creation, and implementation of knowledge management and learning systems that have scaled across 60 countries and has developed video materials for MusAid, an international nonprofit organization, and Population Services International.
